1.subquestion: What is vector $\overrightarrow{AB}$ in terms of vectors $\overrightarrow{OA}$ and $\overrightarrow{OB}$?

subanswer.text: Vector $\overrightarrow{AB}$ can be found by subtracting vector $\overrightarrow{OA}$ from vector $\overrightarrow{OB}$; hence, $\overrightarrow{AB} = \overrightarrow{OB} - \overrightarrow{OA}$. Plugging in the values, we have $\overrightarrow{AB} = \begin{pmatrix}-3 \\ -2 \\ 1\end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix}1 \\ 2 \\ 3\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}-4 \\ -4 \\ -2\end{pmatrix}$. The answer is $\begin{pmatrix}-4 \\ -4 \\ -2\end{pmatrix}$.
